title: Mammoth Cave National Park: Amphibians
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Amphibians                Amphibians         Cave Salamander   Mammoth Cave National Park is home to a variety of salamanders, toads, and frogs. Among the species here are: Salamanders Mudpuppy, Hellbender, Red spotted newt, Jefferson salamander, Spotted salamander, Marbled salamander, Tiger salamander, Zigzag salamander, Slimy salamander, Eastern mud salamander, Northern red salamander, Southern two-lined salamander, Long-tailed salamander, Cave salamander, Northern dusky salamander, Small-mouthed salamander Toads Eastern spadefoot toad, American toad, Fowler's toad Frogs Southern cricket frog, Mountain chorus frog, Spring peeper, Gray treefrog, Bullfrog, Green frog, Pickerel frog, Leopard frog, Wood frog, Eastern narrow-mouthed toad
